tinues to add attackers to e5 with Bc7 or Qc7 or castles to bring their king into safety.} Z0 (12... Qc7 13. Nbd4 {and the pawn on e5 is still poisoned} Ngxe5 $2 14. Nxe5 Nxe5 15. Bf4 f6 16. Qh5+ Kf8 17. Rxe5 $1 {SF15:+5 Black is playing without their two rooks and their king is unsafe. White's plan is Re1-Re3-Rf3/Rg3 with a crushing attack.}) *

