{From variation 5... Bd7 6... f6 [/variation/25627351]} 12... a6 {[%mdl 32768] With the idea of preventing Nb5.} 13. Nb5 {[%csl Yc7][%cal Yb5c7]} ({White ignores the defence and continues} 13. Nb5 {opening up the a-file.}) (13. b4 {is an alternative.}) 13... axb5 14. axb5 {[%csl Ya8][%cal Ya1a8] Opening the a-file with great effect and threatening Ra8. The Black king will not find safety.} Qb6 {[%csl Bc7][%cal Bc8c7] Giving the king an escape square on c7.} 15. c4 dxc4 (15... d4 16. Bd2 {threatening Ba5.}) 16. Ra8+ Kc7 17. Qd6+ {[%csl Yc7][%cal Yd6c7]} Qxd6 {Black is forced to take.} 18. exd6+ Kb6 19. Rxd8 {And White wins 18...Ng6 19.Rxd7 Nxf4 20.Bxc4 .} *

