{This game was played in round 6 of the FIDE Grand Swiss in Riga on November 1, 2021. This tournament was part of the qualification cycle for the World Chess Championship.} 1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. c3 Nc6 5. Nf3 Qb6 6. Bd3 cxd4 7. O-O Bd7 8. Re1 Nge7 9. h4 h6 {We are following 5... Qb6 6... cxd4 7... Bd7 9... h6 [/variation/24553711].} 10. a3 ({Both sides continue to develop their pieces and keep the tension around d4. GM Gawain Jones recommends playing h5 first to prevent a future g5.} 10. h5 Rc8 11. a3 a6 12. b4 dxc3 13. Nxc3 Nxb4 14. Na4 Bxa4 15. Qxa4+ Nbc6 16. Bd2 Qc7 17. Qg4 $13 {White is aiming for immediate queenside expansion with b2-b4 and Bb2.}) 10... Rc8 11. b4 a6 (11... dxc3 12. Nxc3 Nxb4 13. Be3 Qd8 14. axb4 Rxc3 {is approximately equal although it feels like White has the initiative.}) 12. Bb2 g5 $1 {White refrained from playing h5 allowing Black to get the thematic g5 in.} 13. Nh2 {[%csl Bf6,Bg4][%cal Bh2g4,Bg4f6] Why not take on g5 twice?} (13. hxg5 hxg5 14. Nxg5 Nf5 15. Bxf5 exf5 16. cxd4 Ne7 17. Nd2 Qh6 {or}) (13. hxg5 hxg5 14. Nxg5 Nf5 15. Nd2 Ne3 16. Qe2 Nxe5 17. cxd4 Nxd3 18. Qxd3 Qd6) {Both variations highlight the vulnerability of the White king after the h-file has been opened.} 13... Bg7 14. Ng4 {Aiming for Nf6+.} gxh4 15. cxd4 h5 $6 ({Played after 20 minutes of thought: 'long think, wrong think'. Better} 15... Nxd4 {as}) (15... h5 {is only chasing the knight to a square that it wanted to go to in the first place. SF15:+1}) 16. Nf6+ Bxf6 17. exf6 {[%csl Ye7][%cal Yf6e7]} Ng8 {[%csl Yf6][%cal Yg8f6] Saving the knight and attacking the pawn on f6.} 18. Qf3 {[%csl Bf6,Yd5,Be8][%cal Bf3f6,Yf3d5,Be1e8] Defending the pawn on f6 but also threatening Qxd5.} Rh6 $2 ({Now the piece coordination of Black becomes too bad SF15:+2. Black could have held it together with} 18... Qd8 19. Qxd5 Nxf6 20. Qf3 Rg8 {with the idea} 21. d5 e5 $1 22. dxc6 Bxc6 {with Bc6 and Rg8 attacking g2.}) 19. Qxd5 Nxf6 {[%csl Yd5][%cal Yf6d5]} 20. Qg5 {[%csl Yh6][%cal Yg5h6] Attacking Rh6.} Ng4 {[%csl Bh6][%cal Bg4h6]} 21. Nc3 $1 ({Nxd4} 21. Qg8+ Ke7 {Nd5+ with a double attack on Qb6 and Ke7. 21...Qxd4 22.Nd5! Qxf2 23.Kh1 and mate to follow.}) 21... Qd8 22. Qxd8+ Kxd8 23. Ne4 {[%csl Yc8,Yf7,Yd8][%cal Ye4d6,Yd6c8,Yd6f7,Yf7h6,Yf7d8] Threatening Nd6 with a double attack on Rc8 and pawn f7.} e5 {[%csl Bd6][%cal Bh6d6] Defending against Nd6.} 24. f3 {[%csl Yg4][%cal Yf3g4] The knight can only go to f6 interfering with the defense of Rh6 of the square d6.} Nxd4 25. fxg4 hxg4 26. Ng5 {[%csl Yf7,Yd8,Yh6,Ye5][%cal Yg5f7,Yf7d8,Yf7h6,Ye1e5] Threatening Nxf7 and Rxe5.} 1-0

