{This game was played in the seventh round of the U.S. Women's Chess Championship on October 13, 2021. After surprising her opponent with this line in round 2, IM Carissa Yip chose to repeat the line in round 7 and could expect a prepared opponent.} 1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. c3 Qb6 5. Nf3 Bd7 ({If Black plays} 5... Bd7 {without Nc6 their intent is often to go Bb5 to exchange their bad bishop. See variation 4... Qb6 5... Bd7 6... Bb5 [/variation/16909595].}) 6. Bd3 cxd4 7. O-O (7. Nxd4 {preventing Bb5 would have been slightly stronger.}) 7... dxc3 8. Nxc3 Ne7 9. h4 h6 ({The thematic move after Ne7 with the intent of} 9... Ng6 10. h5 {kicking the knight back.}) 10. h5 Qd8 11. Be3 {White is a pawn down but SF15:+1. Compare the lead in development, control of the center and piece activity!} Nec6 12. Rc1 Be7 13. Bb1 Na5 ({With the idea} 13... O-O 14. Qd3 {winning. Black has great difficulty bringing her king into safety and developing Nb8 and Ra8.}) 14. Qd4 {[%csl Bd4,Bg4,Yg7][%cal Bd1d4,Bd4g4,Yg4g7]} Nbc6 15. Qg4 {[%csl Yg7][%cal Yg4g7] 'Queen up and over': Qd1-Qd4-Qg4.} Kf8 {[%csl Bg7][%cal Bf8g7] Defending the pawn on g7 but how will Black get Rh8 into the game?} 16. b3 {Taking away the square c4 for Na5.} Rc8 17. Ne2 $6 ({On move 22 White plays Nb5 eyeing d6. Since White has a space advantage it was best to start this plan without exchanging any pieces first} 17. Nb5 b6 18. Qg3 {with the threat of Nd6.}) 17... b6 18. Rcd1 Rc7 19. Qg3 Bc8 20. Nfd4 Nxd4 21. Nxd4 Nc6 22. Nb5 Rd7 23. f4 d4 24. Bf2 Bc5 $2 ({Black should have prevented f5 by White by playing f5 herself.} 24... f5 25. exf6 gxf6 {and White is better but Black can fight with Rg8 Bb7 and White can not play f5 because after e5 by Black, Black is better.}) 25. f5 $1 {Opening lines in front of the Black king. SF15:+2.} exf5 26. Bxf5 Re7 27. Be4 Nxe5 $2 {Allows for a nice tactical shot by White.} 28. b4 $1 {Luring Bc5 to b4, setting up the double attack Rxd4.} Bxb4 29. Rxd4 {[%csl Yd8,Yb4][%cal Yd4d8,Yd4b4] With a double attack on Bb4 and Qd8 winning a piece.} 1-0

