1. e4 {[%mdl 32768]} e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. c3 Bd7 5. Nf3 Qb6 6. Bd3 Nc6 7. dxc5 Bxc5 8. O-O a5 9. Qe2 Nge7 (9... f6 {If Black decides to delay developing the knight, then we immediately open the center with the explosive c3-c4!} 10. c4 {for example:} d4 11. exf6 Nxf6 12. Bf4 O-O 13. Nbd2 Rae8 14. Ne5 {SF15:+1}) 10. Nbd2 a4 {In the trainable variation 5... Qb6 6... Bd7 8... a5 [/variation/16848816]} ({we look at the more popular move} 10... Ng6 {and now} 11. Nb3 Be7 {. 'White has a pleasant game with good central control' GM Gawain Jones. Evaluation: SF15:1 A sample line: 12...O-O 13.h4 Nxh4? 14.Nxh4 Bxh4 15.Qh5 . SF15:+5}) 11. b4 axb3 12. Nxb3 Ba3 13. Bf4 {Our trainable variation has the following sideline:} (13. Rb1 Qc7 14. Nbd4 {with threat Nb5 with a double attack on Qc7 and Ba3 and after 14... O-O the Greek Gift 15. Bxh7 becomes also an option.}) 13... Qc7 14. Rab1 Na5 15. Nbd4 Qxc3 $6 {Is this pawn poisined or not?} 16. Nc2 $1 {[%csl Ya3,Yd2,Ye3,Yd4,Yc5,Yc3][%cal Yc2a3,Yf4d2,Yc3c5,Yd2e3,Ye3d4] Yes! The knight on c2 attacks Ba3 and White threatens to eliminate the defender Qc3 by Bd2-Qc5-Be3-Qc3-Bd4.} Nec6 17. Rb5 $1 {[%csl Yd2,Rc5][%cal Yf4d2,Rb5c5] Now White threatens to trap Qc3 with Bd2.} Nb4 18. Rxb4 $1 Bxb4 19. Bd2 {[%csl Yb4,Yc3][%cal Yc2b4,Yd2b4] With an X-ray attack of Bd2 on Bb4.} Qb2 20. Bxb4 {White has won a bishop and a knight against a rook (and a pawn soon). Materially speaking this is not too bad but Black's king is still in the middle and White also has a strong bishop pair SF15:+4.} Nc6 {[%csl Re8,Bd3,Bb4] Threatening Nxb4.} 21. Bd6 Rxa2 22. Qd2 {[%csl Yg5][%cal Yd2g5] Threatening Qg5.} h6 {[%csl Rg5][%cal Rh6g5]} 23. h4 Ne7 24. Qe3 Nc8 {[%csl Yd6][%cal Yc8d6] Threatening to take attacker Bd6.} 25. Bb4 Ra4 {[%csl Yb4][%cal Ya4b4,Yb2b4] With a twofold attack on Bb4.} 26. Qd2 {Defending Bb4.} Bc6 27. Nfd4 Kd7 28. Qf4 {[%csl Yf7][%cal Yf4f7] Threatening Qxf7.} Ke8 29. Nb5 f6 30. exf6 Qxf6 31. Qc7 {[%csl Yc8][%cal Yc7c8] Threatening Qxc8.} Bd7 {Defending Nc8.} 32. h5 {[%csl Yg6][%cal Yd3g6] Threatening Bg6+.} Rxb4 33. Nxb4 Qe7 34. Bg6+ Kf8 35. Re1 1-0

